name: Pioneer
desc: Pioneer is a Tier 4 ship in Starblast.io. It fires two lasers from the front at a slightly slow speed that does moderate damage.
author: Neuronality

name: Crusader
desc: Crusader is a Tier 4 ship in Starblast.io. It fires two parallel shots from the nose of the ship that deals a moderate amount of damage
author: Neuronality

name: U-Sniper
desc: The U-Sniper is a Tier 5 ship in Starblast.io. It fires two pulses from the front that do large damage with very large recoil and slight knockback on the victim.
author: Neuronality

name: T-Warrior
desc: T-Warrior is a Tier 5 ship in Starblast.io. It fires five frontal lasers that diverge, and as such is best at close ranges. It is an incredible ship for mining asteroids and can stand on its own against other players in combat.
author: Neuronality

name: FuryStar
desc: FuryStar is a Tier 5 ship in Starblast.io. This was the second instance of a ship design/idea being pulled from the subreddit community and implemented into the game.
author: Starblast-Gpolic

name: Aetos
desc: Aetos is a Tier 5 ship in Starblast.io. It fires two slightly converging side lasers from the front that do moderate damage. It is moderately good at mining asteroids with a good ship speed, but is very weak against enemy vessels unless fully upgraded.
author: Neuronality

name: Shadow X-2
desc: Shadow X-2 is a Tier 5 ship in Starblast.io. It is a Tier 5 version of the Shadow X-1 and X-3, sharing similar characteristics to the X1 more than the X3.
author: Neuronality

name: Howler
desc: The Howler is the newest ship in the vanilla ship tree. It is a Tier 5, on the right side of the tree. It replaced the Toscain on 1/28/2020. It is also a little bit like a mini-Marauder.
author: Malefor

name: Bat-Defender
desc: Bat-Defender is a Tier 5 ship in Starblast.io. It is a tier 5 version of the Crusader, has the highest shield capacity of any Tier 5 ship, and fires 2 side converging lasers from the front.
author: Neuronality

name: Advanced-Fighter
desc: The Advanced-Fighter is a Tier 6 ship in Starblast.io. It fires one frontal pulse with immense damage (equivalent to the pulse of an Aries when maxed) and knockback, and four small side lasers from the front, and like the Shadow X-3, it is a typical glass cannon ship.
author: Neuronality

name: Scorpion
desc: Scorpion is a Tier 6 ship in Starblast.io. It fires one frontal pulse with large damage and knockback, and two small lasers from each side that do almost no damage.
author: Neuronality

name: Marauder
desc: Marauder is a Tier 6 ship in Starblast.io that replaced the H-Mercury. It sacrifices a frontal pulse for a rapidly firing central laser and two side lasers.
author: Dimed, Finalizer

name: Condor
desc: Condor is a Tier 6 ship in Starblast.io. It fires one frontal pulse with moderate damage and knockback as well as two frontal lasers. It has a high rate of fire, which allows it to quickly attack while moving, and is the third-fastest Tier 6 ship, after the Marauder.
author: Neuronality

name: A-Speedster
desc: A-Speedster is a Tier 6 ship in Starblast.io. It fires one frontal pulse with moderate damage, knockback, and recoil as well as two frontal diverging lasers.
author: Neuronality

name: Rock-Tower
desc: Rock-Tower is a Tier 6 ship in Starblast.io. It fires two tiny frontal lasers extremely rapidly, while simultaneously having great ramming damage.
author: Neuronality

name: Barracuda
desc: Barracuda is a Tier 6 ship in Starblast.io. It is a ship meant purely for ramming and fires nothing. Instead, it has an ability called Dash, essentially charging ahead at increased speed to ram, inflicting impact damage.
author: Neuronality

name: O-Defender
desc: O-Defender is a Tier 6 ship in Starblast.io. It has the highest shield capacity and regen among Tier 6's and fires one frontal pulse that does moderate damage and knockback.
author: Neuronality

name: Odyssey
desc: Odyssey is a Tier 7 ship in Starblast.io. It has the second-highest shield capacity and the second-slowest ship speed in the game, both after the Aries. It fires one gigantic frontal pulse that is slow but has the highest laser damage in vanilla currently.
author: Neuronality

name: Shadow X-3
desc: Shadow X-3 is a Tier 7 ship in Starblast.io. It is the Tier 7 version of the Shadow X-2 and Shadow X-1, yet shares a lot of characteristics with the Advanced-Fighter; it is a glass cannon ship which fires one frontal pulse with immense speed, damage, and knockback, as well as 4 small lasers from the sides.
author: Neuronality

name: Bastion
desc: The Bastion is a Tier 7 ship in Starblast that was designed by Kleinem and was added to the game on Aug 4, 2017. It is the only tier 7 ship in Starblast that is a total bullet hose and is most similar to the former H-Mercury (Now replaced with Marauder, also similar to the Bastion).
author: Kleinem

name: Aries
desc: The Aries fires one slow frontal pulse that does gigantic damage and has no recoil, as well as four moderate lasers from the four sides at roughly right angles.
author: Neuronality

name: H-Mercury
desc: H-Mercury is a retired Tier 6 ship in Starblast.io which was replaced by the Marauder. It is also a ship in the KEST mod. It is a Tier 6 version of the Mercury, sacrificing the pulse for one very rapid frontal laser and four converging lasers from the sides.
author: Neuronality

name: Toscain
desc: Toscain was a Tier 5 ship in Starblast.io. It is a unique ship compared to other ships, firing four frontal lasers that diverge with varying angles, and one pulse that has slight knockback to the victim.
author: Neuronality

name: U-Sniper Mk 2
desc: U-Sniper MK 2 is a starting ship (Tier 1) in U-Series. It is very similar to the vanilla U-Sniper, although the U-Sniper MK2 has higher minimum stats, faster speed, and cannons that are closer together.
author: Finalizer

name: U-Cruiser
desc: The U-Cruiser is a Tier 2 ship in the U-Series mod. It has two side cannons which fire high damage pulses and a central cannon which rapidly fires a pulse.
author: Finalizer

name: U-Quad
desc: The U-Quad is a Tier 2 ship in the U-Series mod. It has 2 cannons at the front which each fire two pulses stacked on top of each other.
author: Finalizer

name: U-Penta
desc: The U-Penta is a Tier 3 ship in the U-Series mod. As suggested by its name, it has 5 cannons each firing pulses. The central cannon fires a slightly weaker pulse at a higher rate. Maxing damage on this ship prevents the outer cannons from firing at all, except on burst shots.
img: The U-Penta is a Tier 3 ship in the U-Series mod. As suggested by its name, it has 5 cannons each firing pulses. The central cannon fires a slightly weaker pulse at a higher rate. Maxing damage on this ship prevents the outer cannons from firing at all, except on burst shots.
author: Finalizer

name: U-Spread
desc: The U-Spread is a Tier 3 ship in the U-Series mod. It fires a spread of 5 lasers from all different angles. The main cannon at the front fires a weaker pulse at a higher rate. This ship is a mix of Support and Offense.
author: Finalizer

name: H-Warrior
desc: The H-Warrior is a Tier 3 ship in the U-Series mod. As suggested by its name, the ship takes the shape of the letter : H .
author: Finalizer

name: U-Sentry
desc: The U-Sentry is a Tier 3 ship in the U-Series mod. It has two front cannons which each fires a pulse each rapidly with high recoil, allowing it to escape easily, similar to the vanilla ship, the Shadow X-3.
author: Finalizer

name: U-Arsenal
desc: The U-Arsenal is a Tier 4 ship in the U-Series mod. It is one of the best Tier 4 in the game. It fires a frenzy of 7 pulses all from the front. This gives it high burst damage and makes it a good ship for attacking, and is a decent miner. It has rather terrifying speed for its size, and it can easily kill anything up to a Tier 6.
author: Finalizer

name: U-Interceptor
desc: The U-Interceptor is a Tier 4 ship in the U-Series mod. It fires 4 pulses from the back to propel itself forward as well as a lower damage pulse from the front. It is built for speed, however lacks in agility.
author: Finalizer

name: U-Speeder
desc: The U-Speeder is a Tier 4 ship in the U-Series mod. It has a dual cannon at the front which fires two pulses and a cannon at the back which rapidly fires a low damage pulse. The back cannon's recoil allows this ship to propel itself forward at insane speeds. However agility is a weakness. it can't make tight turns very well, and is purely and offensive-styled ship.
author: Finalizer

name: U-Siege
desc: The U-Siege is a Tier 4 ship in the U-Series mod. It has 4 cannons at the front; a dual cannon which fires 2 pulses rapidly and two central cannons stacked on top of each other which both rapidly fire inaccurate, lower damage pulses.
author: Finalizer

name: U-Punisher
desc: The U-Punisher is a Tier 5 ship in the U-Series mod. The U-Punisher falls in the Assault ship category. It fires a frenzy of 9 lasers all from the front which have insane recoil. Because of the recoil, this ship can escape easily and combined with its high burst damage makes it a great ship for attacking, due to it being so overpowered.
author: Finalizer

name: U-Octa
desc: The U-Octa is a tier 5 ship in the U-Series mod. This is an excellent miner and attacker! This ship fires a total of 8 bullets in every direction, or in one direction, depending on how you choose to upgrade.
author: Finalizer

name: Trailblazer
desc: The Trailblazer is a tier 5 ship in the U-Series mod. This ship is similar to the U-Demon, but it is much smaller and has much less recoil! It regains energy faster than the U-Demon, moves far faster, and is heavier, but the agility is slightly worse.
author: Finalizer

name: U-Demon
desc: The U-Demon is a tier 5 in the U-Series mod. This ship has similar abilities to the U-Punisher, where it has immense recoil, but very damaging lasers. There is a twist, however. It has cannons on the back which make it double as a bullet dasher, with moderate speed compared to the other speedsters of U-Series. This Ship is best used on the offensive, not defensive, and is mediocre at mining.
author: Finalizer

name: U-Pulsar
desc: The U-Pulsar is a tier 5 ship in the U-Series mod. This ship operates like a glass cannon, being quite fragile with its low shields and mass. However, the two slow 'pulsars' that it fires each cause MASSIVE amounts of damage, being able to take down even the U-Octa's shields.
author: Finalizer

name: U-Barricade
desc: The U-Barricade is a tier 6 in the U-Series mod. Similar to the U-Bruiser, it features immense power and recoil, but it has poor agility. While fast, it accelerates slowly.
author: Finalizer

name: U-Monitor
desc: The U-Monitor is a tier 6 ship in the U-Series mod. This ship is another mining base ship with great attack power and a great fire rate! This ship is very formidable as a healer mainly because of its side lasers. This ship can shoot from the starboard side.
author: Finalizer

name: U-Perimeter
desc: The U-Perimeter is a tier 6 ship in the U-Series mod. This ship is an excellent miner, but this ship is pretty slow and very bulky.
author: Finalizer

name: U-Bruiser
desc: The U-Bruiser is a tier 6 ship in the U-Series mod. This ship a generic power house, with eight powerful lasers. But with great power comes disadvantages: it is very slow and its bullets can be dodged pretty easily.
author: Finalizer

name: U-Afterburn
desc: The U-Afterburn is a Tier 6 ship in the U-Series mod. It shoots two high damage pulses from the front while using its back lasers to propel itself forward at insane speeds.
author: Finalizer

name: U-Smasher
desc: The U-Smasher is a tier 6 in the U-Series mod. This ship is an excellent rammer that goes very fast with its canons in the back. This ship is a much better version of the Barracuda and it shreds most ships if caught unexpected.
author: Finalizer

name: Hellfire
desc: This ship is known for its very high fire rate and stunning abilities! One stream of attacks from this thing can leave an opponent defenseless! Initially, it may face some risks, but when maxed, it can destroy pretty much anything, including Tier 7 ships). But it does have some drawbacks such as its slow speed. But, if any ship gets cornered, they'll probably be shredded.
author: Finalizer

name: U-10 Thunder
desc: The U-10 Thunder is tier 6 ship in the U-Series mod. This ship is like a heavily upgraded U-Sentry, being a bigger version with much faster firerate and damage making it very useful in team battles! However, the amount of damage it can hit at once is limited due to the high recoil per shot, so you need to time your shots well, or you will blast yourself into the void.
author: Finalizer

name: U-Wall
desc: The U-Wall is a Tier-7 ship in the U-Series mod, upgrading from the U-Barricade and U-Monitor. It fires a wave of bullets spanning the length of the entire ship, with bullet speed gradually decreasing away form the center. It is the largest ship in the mod, as well as the second fastest Tier-7, despite its size.
author: Finalizer

name: Heartbreaker
desc: The Heartbreaker is Tier-7 ship in the U-Series mod, and upgrades from the U-Barricade, U-Monitor, U-Perimeter, and the U-Bruiser. It has medium-high power cannons all across its circular body to shower a heart-shaped pattern of bullets around it. The Heartbreaker is the fastest turning Tier-7 in the mod.
author: Finalizer

name: U-Fusion
desc: The U-Fusion is a tier 7 ship in the U-Series mod, upgrading from the U-Perimeter, U-Bruiser, U-Afterburn, and U-Smasher.
author: Finalizer

name: U-Marksman
desc: The U-Marksman is a tier 7 ship in the U-Series mod, upgrading from the U-Afterburn, U-Smasher, Hellfire, and U-10 Thunder. This tier 7 ship is designed to be a sniper, shooting a single extremely heavy and fast shot at enemies with no other weapons other than a small rapid fire beam-type laser that deals the damage of an energy-empty un-upgraded Fly (10 DPS) and mostly exists in spirit of a laser sight.
author: Finalizer

name: Shadow X-27
desc: Shadow X-27 is a tier 7 in the U-Series mod. This ship is very similar to the U-Pulsar but it has none of the disadvantages that the Pulsar had other than the aspect of fragile compared to the other Tier 7's.
author: Finalizer
